 238:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c **** /* The item value of the event list item is normally used to hold the priority
 239:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c ****  * of the task to which it belongs (coded to allow it to be held in reverse
 240:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c ****  * priority order).  However, it is occasionally borrowed for other purposes.  It
 241:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c ****  * is important its value is not updated due to a task priority change while it is
 242:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c ****  * being used for another purpose.  The following bit definition is used to inform
 243:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c ****  * the scheduler that the value should not be changed - in which case it is the
 244:Middlewares/FreeRTOS/source/tasks.c ****  * responsibility of whichever module is using the value to ensure it gets set back
